com.camerontec.catalys.core.message

Class SmartFIXMessageFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.util.configuration.registry.Registerable
      • com.camerontec.catalys.core.message.SmartFIXMessageFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IFIXMessageFactory, ISmartFIXMessageFactory, IRegisterable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MDSmartFIXMessageFactoryImpl, UnsignedSmartFIXMessageFactory

    public class SmartFIXMessageFactory
extends Registerable
implements ISmartFIXMessageFactory
    Default implementation of ISmartFIXMessageFactory.

    Note that FIX messages created by this factory will not contain any header fields. The factory concerns itself with business content only (i.e. body tags), ignoring all FIX session level (i.e. header) tags. This is because the factory has no access to FIX session level information or the context in which the messages are created, and thus should not make any decision about the content of FIX header tags. It leaves this task to session/higher level code which has the necessary context to populate header tags with the correct values.

      • createFIXFill

        public IFIXMessage createFIXFill(ITagValues order,
                                 Decimal quantity,
                                 Decimal price,
                                 String execID,
                                 Decimal avgPx,
                                 Decimal cumQty)
        Description copied from interface: ISmartFIXMessageFactory
        Basic fill execution report is created using values taken from order and the given field values.

        LeavesQty on fill is calculated as order's OrderQty minus the given CumQty.

        See also the other createFIXFill method which computes CumQty and AvgPx by adding the given quantity and price to the CumQty and AvgPx field values in the given order.

        Note that the order itself is not updated (eg CumQty, AvgPx, LeavesQty).

        Specified by:
        createFIXFill in interface ISmartFIXMessageFactory
        Parameters:
        order - Order on which fill is based.
        quantity - Quantity of this trade (LastShares).
        price - Price of this trade (LastPx).
        execID - Execution report execid - should be unique.
        avgPx - Average price of all fills on this order.
        cumQty - Total executed quantity for this order.
        Returns:
        Fill execution report.

      • createFIXFillCancel

        public IFIXMessage createFIXFillCancel(ITagValues order,
                                       ITagValues fill,
                                       String execID)
        Description copied from interface: ISmartFIXMessageFactory
        Creates a cancel for a given fill in a given order.

        Basic fill cancel execution report is created using values taken from order and the fill. Fields such as CumQty, AvgPx and LeavesQty are calculated from their initial values as given in the order and the quantity and price being cancelled as given in the fill.

        Note that the order is not updated (eg CumQty, AvgPx, LeavesQty).

      • setDictionaryName

        public void setDictionaryName(String dictionaryName)
        Description copied from interface: IFIXMessageFactory
        Set the name of the dictionary to be used for dictionary-based validation (e.g. repeating groups) of messages created by this factory. Message factories usually take care of setting the correct dictionaryName of all messages they create. However, in FIX 5.0+ multiple FIX versions are possible over the same session. If you want to make use of this functionality your custom message processors must set the correct dictionaryName on the message overriding the default coming from the factory.

        Note: Message factories can only be configured with one dictionary name. In FIX 5.0+ however it is possible to exchange messages with different FIX versions over the same session. In that case your code must ensure that the messages are populated with the right dictionary name.

        Specified by:
        setDictionaryName in interface IFIXMessageFactory
        Parameters:
        dictionaryName - The name of the dictionary - This must match the XML dictionary file name without the extension .xml. By default under resources/dictionary. The name is case-insensitive an usually of the form FIX.[VERSION], for example FIX.4.0, FIX.4.4, FIX.5.0SP1.

      • setUseExactFixDictionary

        public void setUseExactFixDictionary(boolean useExactFixDictionary)
        Description copied from interface: IFIXMessageFactory
        Set attribute to control whether session dictionary should be used when importing raw FIX bytes. By default the session will use the dictionary of the latest version of FIX when importing raw FIX bytes. This allows users to use fields from later versions of FIX in sessions configured to use earlier FIX versions. Set this value to true if you would like to use the dictionary of the FIX version of this session. You might need to do this if you use custom fields in your messages that are defined differently by a later version of the FIX protocol.
        Specified by:
        setUseExactFixDictionary in interface IFIXMessageFactory
        Parameters:
        useExactFixDictionary - true or false; default is false

      • copyFIXSenderTargetIDs

        public void copyFIXSenderTargetIDs(ITagValues src,
                                   ITagValues dest,
                                   boolean swap)
        Description copied from interface: ISmartFIXMessageFactory
        Copies all the Sender, Target, OnBehalfOf and DeliverTo IDs from one ITagValues to another.

        These fields are SenderCompID, SenderSubID, SenderLocationID, TargetCompID, TargetSubID, TargetLocationID, DeliverToCompID, DeliverToSubID, DeliverToLocationID, OnBehalfOfCompID, OnBehalfOfSubID, OnBehalfOfLocationID.

        If swap is true, the Sender id values in the source are copied to the corresponding Target ids in the destination, the Target IDs are copied to the Sender IDs, the DeliverTo IDs are copied to the OnBehalfOf IDs and the OnBehalfOfIds are copied DeliverTo IDs. This is what normally happens when, for example, a fill is sent back in response to an order. The fill messages will have IDs swapped around from the IDs in the order.

        Specified by:
        copyFIXSenderTargetIDs in interface ISmartFIXMessageFactory
        Parameters:
        src - Contains values to be copied to the dest.
        dest - Values are copied here from the src.
        swap - If true target id's become sender id's and vice versa.
